The paper presents a method for improving generative models' ability to adapt to new distributions, which is a common problem in machine learning. The method involves using a doubly-amortized variational inference procedure, which is a technique used in probabilistic modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also deals with image classification tasks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as well. Finally, the use of transferable latent representations suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
